Subject: in_dxf: HATCH.has_derived must OR every path flag, not just the last

has_derived controls whether pixel_size is written/read. in_dxf set it with
`o->has_derived = flag & 4` per path, so it ended up holding only the LAST
path's derived bit. The decoder computes has_derived as the OR of every
path flag's 0x4 bit. When an earlier path was derived but the last was not
(e.g. flags [7, 24]), the encoder skipped pixel_size while the reader
expected it -> the 64-bit gap corrupted num_seeds and the HATCH became
unreadable. Accumulate with |=.

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

--- a/src/in_dxf.c
+++ b/src/in_dxf.c
@@ HATCH path flag 92
           is_plpath = pair->value.u & 2;
-          o->has_derived = pair->value.u & 4;
+          o->has_derived |= (pair->value.u & 4) ? 1 : 0;
